node.text: @marcellomilanezi see my comment, I think you are exaggerating and I think she was criticising anarchist escapism, intentionally or not

@jameswbirmingham also, how do you select who is on the board? Does being on the board give you some level of authority? Have you read State and Revolution in good faith? Have you read Imperialism? I'm asking because they are relevant to this conversation and to contemporary political and economic analysis.

💫Worlds of Ursula K. Le Guin (2018, 68min)

The remarkable life and legacy of the late anarchist author, Ursula K. Le Guin hasn’t been captured on film…until now.

Produced with Le Guin’s participation over the course of a decade, the film is a journey through the writer’s career and her worlds, both real and fantastic.

Directed by Arwen Curry
Watch now on Means TV ✨
@means_tv it's almost like she wrote a book to inspire thought, not a blueprint for cut and paste cronies
@means_tv just let me be a hater 😔
@sinisteroveralls given how capitlaism has organized health care any other system would obviously do better.  Bad example to choose
look guys, I hate to say it but; if the best case you can make for anarchism is that it has to take place on some fictional moon inhabited by refugees, I don’t know how solid your theory is.
@marcellomilanezi see my comment, I think you are exaggerating and I think she was criticising anarchist escapism, intentionally or not

I think the striking plint, that makes her work potentially realist, is that anarchist moon is far from utopic: there is violence, corruption and research is stiffled. That is how our protagonist leaves it for the capitalist planet dreaming of how his research can the  be shared - only to find even more violence, corruption, persecution and treachery… It’s an amazing work, actually cried near the end when he meets at the (actual) Earth embassy and ahoota some truths at the representative’s face
@justinerickson2099 on Means TV!
Where can I watch??
I went out and bought a tv antenna specifically to watch this when it aired on PBS. It is great. Glad it found a home on means.

@g_u_y_s_e_r I literally curate an imprint through AK Press. I'll be the first to admit anarchists on the Internet don't read enough. Neither do Marxists though. There's a reading problem across all of the left.
@g_u_y_s_e_r actually I think they read more of their books than we do.
@jamsie_po absolutely untrue.
Anarchist read a book challenge 🤣🤣
@sid121199 tanks. That gets us tanks.  When your side runs a state we'll enough that you can get tanks I will listen to you.  Otherwise I will just come to the anarchists for really good cafés

@jameswbirmingham lol, anarchism is a liberal ideology. It is, in action, counter-revolutionary, idealist and impracticable. Little wonder it is a popular option for western liberals. I'm not being hyperbolic. I have done the reading and do know the history.

@jameswbirmingham also, how do you select who is on the board? Does being on the board give you some level of authority? Have you read State and Revolution in good faith? Have you read Imperialism? I'm asking because they are relevant to this conversation and to contemporary political and economic analysis.
No need to promote liberalism.
Thank you for covering anarchist content as well.
A libertarian walks into a bear
@jameswbirmingham  irrelevant
@zera.bloom it’s a troll. Deprive it of oxygen ❤️
@zera.bloom lmao, left-communism go brrr. Literally just lib propaganda with an anarchist aesthetic.
There isn’t such a thing. So forget it and focus on socialism…
@yazidht1991 actually yeah, that does follow anarchist theory. I never thought of that.
I didn't know white flight was a form of anarchism 💀
@shg_motorworks Read the book, you won't regret it.
@shg_motorworks nah, anarchism works fine organization.  The issue is that they can't defend themselves well.
I believe the only way this is remotely possible is in an agrarian pre industrial society without currency. However, as history shows, even within these boundaries tribalism thrives

@jameswbirmingham what evidence do you have that a stateless society works. Communism has US CIA intervention to blame for Communism faltering, anarchism can't get past reality. White westerners love to push anarchism when the Global South demands Communism

@josendhelp the vast majority of societies throughout history and prehistory weren't States which is a particular form of polity. Marx's goal was also a stateless society he just thought you needed a State to get there and eventually abolish itself. Unfortunately Bakunin was right, power corrupts and that's why we need to build political structures with as much horizontalism as possible.

@jameswbirmingham how did that work out for them?  There is a utility in a government being able to do things.  Power doesn't corrupt.  That is a liberal myth.  Corrupt people seek power.  So you are right it is a dangerous tool.  Just like your societies mastered fire a successful revolution will have to master power.
Anarchists and Communists have the same end goal but Anarchists don't want to do the necessary socialism to get to the moneyless, classless society

@rosegoldroy My point is every criticism you've leveled at anarchism has been empty and just shows an ignorance about the subject. There are different programmes and platforms for various anarchist groups. This is no different than there being dozens of strains of Marxism and related state communist positionalities. Anarchist Catalonia was a reference to the Spanish Civil War frankly if you don't know the basics of that history I have no idea what you actually do know about leftist history in general. No where do I say "live and let live" and if you think I'm going to lay out some sort of "plan" on a Meta platform you're either naive AF or a fed. There are organized and disciplined anarchists just like there are organized and disciplined Marxists. But the vast majority of both self-identified folks of both are keyboard warriors who have surface level knowledge through memes and YouTube.

@jameswbirmingham Lol I didn't mean a step by step political plan that you personally are undertaking but I respect the gambit. By side-stepping this glaring issue you can call your ideological opponent a "fed". Fair enough. Here's what I know - you're referring to the Anarchist Catalonia of the 1930s as an example of a successful anarchist program. Meanwhile, we have multiple examples of Marxist-Leninism, most notably China, which are in the primary stage of socialism and lifting millions out of poverty. It seems to me one line of thought is a circle-jerk ideology with little success IRL and the other is a practical science being implemented and sustaining itself right now. And before you go on aboutt the details of the Dengist revisions, I don't give af. China is in the primary stage of socialism being managed by a communist party. Beyond that, Idc what other westerners have to say about it since we have few recent achievements to stand on. We ought to be taking notes.

@rosegoldroy China is a better model than what we have here, though I'd argue Cuba is too despite being "the West." As are the Zapatistas if we want to chat about something contemporary and in the spectrum of anarchist thought.  I think we can do better than the examples of actually existing socialism whether China, Vietnam or Kerala. As I mentioned elsewhere on this post I'm on the board of directors of The Institute for Anarchist Studies, as a 'big tent' anarchist org and a public facing anarchist scholar I don't advocate for one anarchist tendency over another publicly.  I'll say the biggest differences between anarchist prefigurative strategy right now and what I see the big ML groups doing is we obviously aren't running presidential candidates and the like. We're generally looking at resilience strategies for dealing with the climate catastrophe and evasion as an alternative to directly confronting state power (see Graeber on Madagascar).
Anarchism skips a step 🤷‍♂️ won't work
@a_noncarnivorous_cat *the

I read tut dispossessed as a criticism of anarchist escapism and idealism, because it hasn't been a great success and when he goes back things are worse than ever. That's why you need an organised revolution not anarchist separatism. The story makes it overt that they didn't escape capitalism, they just ran away from it.
